Barcelona	Make a copy of your passport to take with you when exploring the city	Bring enough of all prescription medications you may need while on vacation	Pack sunscreen, especially when traveling to Barcelona in the warmer spring and summer months	Pack comfortable walking shoes and lightweight clothing that can be worn all day	include a bathing suit in your baggage	Bring a warm coat if you are heading to Barcelona between October and February	Include an umbrella	Bring a European electrical outlet adapter
Zaragoza	The best time to visit Zaragoza is during spring (April to mid-June) and autumn (Sept-Oct).	A Zaragoza card can be bought which gives a lot of offers.						
Malaga	Buy Spanish phrase book and/or dictionary.	Wear a hat to protect yourself from sunstroke during the extremely hot summer sun and carry suntan lotion	There are also several tourist holiday resorts within reach: Torremolinos, Nerja and Marbella.					
Paris	Bring clothes that you can layer: a T-shirt, a sweater to wear over it, a jacket or coat on top of that. And yes, this applies even in July.	An umbrella is handy.	Comfortable shoes are a must as most of the exploring takes place on foot	Bring your own bottled water when walking through the city as purchasing water may be expensive	Baisc knowledge of french will go a long way. Eg. "parlez vous anglais" -pronunciation:Parlay voo onglai = "Do you speak english?" before you commence a conversation would help break the ice	Always greet someone before starting a conversation. Bonjour for good morning and bonsair for good evening	Paris boasts of one of the most widespread underground transit systems in the world. It is extremely well connected though figuring out the map may be a little challenging.	People in France are very courteous. Merci (thank you) and pardon (asking for forgiveness - sorry or excuse me) are two very oft heard words - especially in the metro
Lyon	In the summer, it can get really hot. In the winter, it can get really cold. Hence pack accordingly and  regardless of when you travel, bring an umbrella.	Try to carry an English- French or your Local language to French Dictionary.	Bring your own bottled water when walking through the city.					
Marseille	Suntan lotion/block is recommended	Bring some medicine with you to combat the debilitating effects of diarrhea as it is common	Note that there are many reports of mugging and pickpocketing so avoid carrying valuables and always be aware of your surroundings.					
