Rome	A comfortable, well-made pair of shoes.	During the winter, early spring and late fall, Rome can reach below-freezing temperatures; pack your warmest winter jacket, gloves and hat for these months.	Bring a light fleece jacket for cool summer evenings.	Umbrella is very useful.	Pack all prescription medicines in their original, labeled packages, and bring painkillers for headaches or muscle aches	To avoid getting lost in Rome, bring a guidebook to the city.	Taking tours of the famous monuments maybe interesting albeit a little expensive. Audio guides may be a good alternative(much cheaper) but not nearly as much fun.	Trevi fountain looks ethereal at night and is worth a visit
Naples	Luggage with wheels may not be such a great idea here because of all the cobbles	You’ll want to dress in layers	Take comfortable flat shoes to help you cope with all those cobbles	An umbrella or a waterproof coat is preferable along with sunscreen & sunglasses.	you’ll need to bring prescription medicines	Beware of pick-pockets and slightly rough locals		
